      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LONG SERVICE LEAF (4) showed plenty of talent in his debut campaign, jumping a $4.40 chance in a good race before the break. His two trials coming in have been solid and Chris Parnham sticks from those heats. The inside draw should see him prominent in the run and he can make an impact on his return. ART SESSION (2) bolted in at the trials recently after missing as an odds-on favourite at Geraldton to end last campaign. He's placed in both attempts over this course and distance and as well as 2/3 when fresh. Looks back in top order and can resume with a bang. FIRST BEACH (1) pulled up with an issue last start when well beaten, racing in stronger company to begin his campaign. He's third-up now and should appreciate this easier company. Given some time between runs and he can bounce back to his best. UNDER INFLUENCE (3) gets Pike in the saddle on resumption and can't be discounted. GOLD VANCOUVER (5) is next best.",
